content.description:
Sit start with hands on the obvious rails, left foot around the arete on a mossy chip almost all the way under the boulder, and right foot on the face. Bump up into one of the many pockets and follow the left side of the face to the top out. 

*The crack and large pockets on the right hand side of the face are OFF**
content.protection: The landing is slightly rocky but not atrocious, a single pad works well. Some may consider it a bit of a high ball but it's pretty mellow.
content.location: Head 75 yds due north out of the hollow and you will run smack dab into this beautiful 20+ ft tall sandstone boulder with smooth water markings down one face.

content.description: Short little finger crack and an arete, three moves or so. It gets a little tougher if you climb just the crack.
content.protection: A pad, or a spotter, or nothing. The landing is very clean.
content.location: North of the slackjaw boulder about 20 feet.

content.description: Sit start on the large crack on the right side of the boulder. Follow the crack and jugs to the top. The last few feet are a bit harder but all in all its an easy send.
content.protection: The landing is rocky, bring a pad.

content.description: SDS matched on a small edge under the overhang. Punch to the start holds of Moonshine, then continue climbing powerful moves up the steep overhang.
Taller than it is wide, and characterized by a uniquely "polished" surface.  You'll love this rock!
